Hi Dan,

We hope everyone on your side is self and well.

Here at NE, our tech team is currently checking the update to the latest version 2020.1.LTS. Stephan and I are simultaneously working on the custom question templates. However, we want to come to a conclusion by the end of this week and as soon as the updates are running, we will fix the custom settings in the templates.

In this context we have some questions again. The most important issue concerns the already created questions. What happens to them after implementation of the new custom question templates?

In detail, the following questions came up:

1. Is it possible to change the settings of already created questions/items globally to the settings, which are fixed by the custom templates?
2. What happens with settings that have existing values or text in a field, for example in the more options category, but this field will be later hidden in the UI of the new custom templates?
3. What happens to questions created with question templates, which are not part of the new question templates anymore Can we still edit them?
4. Is there a solution on your side, or is it the task of our dev team to find a solution (if so, how did other customers solve this problem)?
We would be very happy about a short-term video call with you, for example tomorrow morning or afternoon. We think it is easier and faster to explain our questions and concerns orally rather than in written form. Your feedback and estimation would really help us to plan the next steps.

Thank you in advance!

All the best,
Christina and Stephan

--

Hi Stephan & Christina,

I just want to clarify a couple of things. My understanding is that you have, for example, a custom question template that you created a number of Items from. You now wish to amend some setting(s) in the custom question template, while simultaneously updating the set of Items you created based on this template.

  The most important issue concerns the already created questions. What happens to them after implementation of the new custom question templates?
  To put your mind at ease, once an Item is created and saved, your future amendments to the custom template(s) from which it was based will not affect the previously created Item. 

With that said, you can change your custom question templates while not affecting your current content, however, if you do wish to update your current Items, you can do so using Item Bank Endpoints.

  Is it possible to change the settings of already created questions/items globally to the settings, which are fixed by the custom templates? 
>>> Yes, you can do this using Item Bank Endpoints for saved Items.  What happens with settings that have existing values or text in a field, for example in the more options category, but this field will be later hidden in the UI of the new custom templates? 
>>> Changing the question templates will not affect content created and saved in your Itembank.  What happens to questions created with question templates, which are not part of the new question templates anymore Can we still edit them?
>>> Yes you can still edit Items created from a template you no longer wish to include in your new custom question templates.  Is there a solution on your side, or is it the task of our dev team to find a solution (if so, how did other customers solve this problem)?
>>> Can you give me some more information here? I believe the Item bank endpoints, linked above will solve your issue, however, let me know if I am missing something.  
Best,
Emily

subject: Can I create an Item branching assessments in Learnosity OOTB directly?

comments.body:
Hi,

I'm wondering whether I can create item branching assessments directly in OOTB Learnosity without API input.

I understand there are instructions about how to create branching assessment.

What I focus on is to create this directly in Learnosity using the existing UI.

Pls advise.

Many thanks,
Xiaohong

Hi, 

 I'm wondering whether I can create item branching assessments directly in OOTB Learnosity without API input. 

 I understand there are instructions about how to create branching assessment. 

 What I focus on is to create this directly in Learnosity using the existing UI. 

 Pls advise. 

 Many thanks,

Xiaohong

HI Xiaohong,

Just to clarify, Learnosity is the name of the company, and we have several products and APIs. When you say "existing UI" combined with no API, do you mean the shared author site?

Rich

Hi Rich, 

   

 Yes, I meant the Author site. 

   

 Thanks, 

 Xiaohong 

   

 ---

Xiaohong Zhu 

 Asset Management & Distribution 

 Pearson 

   

 xiaohong.zhu@pearson.com 

   

   

 From: "Rich Shupe (Learnosity Author Guide)" <support@learnosityauthorguide.zendesk.com>

Reply-To: Learnosity Author Guide <support+id13897@learnosityauthorguide.zendesk.com>

Date: Tuesday, April 28, 2020 at 2:23 PM

To: "Zhu, Xiaohong" <xiaohong.zhu@pearson.com>

Subject: [Pearson Core Platforms] Re: Can I create an Item branching assessments in Learnosity OOTB directly?

HI XIaohong,

We don't have a graphic tool, such as a flowchart or drag and drop utility, to create item branching assessments. But you can edit the JSON and paste it into the Advanced tab (JSON source) in the activity builder.

All forms of adaptive testing require intermediate to advanced knowledge and are developer-driven, so JSON editing will be required.

I hope this helps,
Rich

Hi Rich, 

   

 Thanks for the update. 

   

 So, to confirm there is no ready-to-use activity template for us to configure the branching. We have to edit the JSON in the Advanced tab so as to make the branching feature work. 

   

 Are these the specific JSON update to the activity? https://help.learnosity.com/hc/en-us/articles/360000755618-Building-Item-Branching-Assessments 

   

 Is there a simple sample that you could provide in JSON format so that I can paste it in Advanced tab and show my manager and peers? 

   

 Thanks again, 

 Xiaohong 

   

 ---

Xiaohong Zhu 

 Asset Management & Distribution 

 Pearson 

   

 xiaohong.zhu@pearson.com 

   

   

 From: "Rich Shupe (Learnosity Author Guide)" <support@learnosityauthorguide.zendesk.com>

Reply-To: Learnosity Author Guide <support+id13897@learnosityauthorguide.zendesk.com>

Date: Tuesday, April 28, 2020 at 5:05 PM

To: "Zhu, Xiaohong" <xiaohong.zhu@pearson.com>

Subject: [Pearson Core Platforms] Re: Can I create an Item branching assessments in Learnosity OOTB directly?

Hi Xiaohong,

Correct, adaptive testing requires, at minimum trained authors, and/or developers and psychometricians, depending on the flavor of adaptive you want to use. Item doesn't require the difficulty level or ability estimates that item adaptive requires, so no psychometricians are needed. But it does require JSON.

Yes, that help document is how to author item branching. You can see a demo, including source examples, here. And you can watch a webinar about Learnosity adaptive options here.

I hope this helps,
Rich

Hello, we're updating our code to 2020.2.LTS for 6/1 (or maybe 2020.1.LTS if we should go earlier, depending on what yall think). Right now we have the capacity to test only a certain portion of our services, so we will not be able to upgrade certain services for a few weeks. If we have items being created by the latest data end point (be it 2020.1.LTS or 2020.2.LTS) will we still be able to load them through the items API if that service is using 2018.2.LTS or will that cause issues?
Also, we've been trying to track down where in our code has been calling questions 2.113.0 and data 1.25. Is it possible that those API's are being called by a different API version under the hood? Unlikely, but I haven't been able to locate any place in our code that is explicitly calling those versions. Thanks!

Hello, we're updating our code to 2020.2.LTS for 6/1 (or maybe 2020.1.LTS if we should go earlier, depending on what yall think). Right now we have the capacity to test only a certain portion of our services, so we will not be able to upgrade certain services for a few weeks. If we have items being created by the latest data end point (be it 2020.1.LTS or 2020.2.LTS) will we still be able to load them through the items API if that service is using 2018.2.LTS or will that cause issues?

Also, we've been trying to track down where in our code has been calling questions 2.113.0 and data 1.25. Is it possible that those API's are being called by a different API version under the hood? Unlikely, but I haven't been able to locate any place in our code that is explicitly calling those versions. Thanks!

Hi Hudson,

Creating content in a later version than you're using to deliver the assessment will likely cause problems. For example, think of authoring a question type that was introduced in 2020.1 and not available to an assessment using 2018.2.

Other APIs can call Questions API, but that's likely not the case with the Data API.

Rich
Okay, that makes sense, thanks Rich. Should we upgrade to 2020.1.LTS? Or can we go straight to 2020.2.LTS?

Hudson,

2020.2.LTS won't be released by June 1, and you'll want to leave as much time for testing as you can. We recommend 2020.1.LTS in your situation.

Thanks,
Rich

At what point is a question ID created and is there any way we can copy a question to a new item and carry the question ID forward?  (We realize that making Items within Activities--rather than Questions within Items--would have been the better way to manage this.)

At what point is a question ID created and is there any way we can copy a question to a new item and carry the question ID forward?  (We realize that making Items within Activities--rather than Questions within Items--would have been the better way to manage this.)

Karen,

A question ID is created at the time the question is created. And its correct to place a question within an item, and an item within an activity, so you’ve done everything right. There’s typically no item without question or activity without item.

Why do you want to copy the question reference?

Rich

Hi Rich, 

 We’d like to create a new item that includes some existing questions plus a new one. We’d like to maintain the question IDs so that we can connect new data from those existing questions with data we already have from them. 

 Karen

Hi Karen,

I'll have to talk to three teams about this: authoring, assessment, and analytics to try to get some input. Briefly, there's no way in the authoring front end systems to do what you're asking. There may be a way for your developers to do this using a data API, but it's not a recommended workflow.

Can you describe what kind of data you're talking about? I ask because most data in the Learnosity ecosystem is item-centric. I'm not sure I understand what data you could be referring to that would be tied to a question reference.

Thanks,
Rich

Hi Rich, 

 It helps to know that there’s no way to do this in the authoring front end. I’m checking with one of our developers on alternatives. 

 Our data downloads include Item IDs and for each question the ID is followed by a set of random digits. We were thinking we might be able assign (or maintain) those digits across items. But I think we’ll find another way to go. 

 Thanks so much for your help. 

 Best,

Karen

Hi Karen,

I still don't have a lot of context around what data you're trying to mine, and would like to help if I can. There may be ways to do that at the item level. But you're right, you might have enough info to move in another direction and that might preclude a protracted conversation. Just know that you can reach out if you want to discuss how you might implement something.

Best,
Rich

Hi Robert,

It's true that scoring is async to ensure submissions are always saved and there's no data loss. Scoring, and therefore, Firehose messages, will never occur immediately after submission.  However, delays of 15-30 minutes are not close to what might be expected. 

Reducing your save frequency will definitely have a significant impact. Customers must be able to query/report on in-progress sessions, so every sessions goes through the scoring queue with every save. Changing saves from every 1 (read 5) second(s) to every 60 seconds will be a twelve-fold reduction in the number of sessions in the scoring queue. Considering the first AP exams are May 11, and students are prepping now, the sooner that can be done, the better.

Review
First, I'll describe where review and Firehose sit in the process, at a high level. When a session is initialized, we capture the questions and responses (hereafter "captured") to support various features. That data is not exposed to you via the Data API/Firehose until you save or submit (hereafter "saved"), but it exists in a very behind-the-scenes way.

Test
A session can be resumed, or reviewed, immediately after capture, before Data/Firehose is a part of the picture. You can test this by reinitializing a session in review mode, from within the readyListener of the first init. You will find that the session successfully re-inits in review mode, without 10005 errors, without even pressing the Start button. This is fairly strong info in our case because no save or submit persisted the data or triggered a Firehose message.

Quick Fix
While we strongly encourage you to continue in your efforts to clarify your workflow, you can add the captureOnResumeError property (see my post from yesterday at 17:40) and you won't receive the 10005 errors anymore.

Please let me know what you think or if it will help to jump on a call.

Hi Mikolaj,

The Product Owner and dev team have discussed this bug, and have come back to me with more information.

The activity configuration for Sections is limited to regions and region overrides. It does not support having different timers for different sections.
They explained that it was an oversight in our documentation and they will update the docs to reflect the limitations and outline specifically what is supported by sections.

They also said they would love to know more about your use case, if you can provide some detail of the workflow, and why it is necessary, so that we can consider this for future development.

Thanks,

Hello, 

 I don't know exactly when it started to happen, but we're getting json timeout responses (with 200 code) in https://eventbus.learnosity.com/latest/subscribe requests and this is preventing our "Live Progress" feature in assessments to work.

There is a chrome HAR file attached to help you understand. 

 Is there a way to pin the version, instead of using always `latest` and get a stable response?  

 Schoology credentials (if needed):

Login page - https://app.schoology.com/login

User - learnositytest@example.com

Password - password 

 Steps to reproduce in Schoology:

- Click on `Live Progress` tab and open Chrome Dev Tools

- On `network` page, the `authentication` request is fine, the `lastevents` request is fine, but the `subscribe` request keep returning timeout.

Hi Hugo,

Can you tell me where you're specifying latest?

We looked at some stats and we don't think the problem is with the version. We think the problem is that you're flooding the Event bus using the events many times more than you need to. We think you might be turning the Events API on for every single assessment, every time it's initialized, rather than only when you are using the Live Progress report for proctoring.

The reason we think this is that you're publishing 150 to 200 times more than you're subscribing. We think all assessments might be publishing events without a corresponding proctor to listen for them. Either that, or there's something wrong with the publish logic and you're manually publishing 200 events for every init. In either case, the Event bus is trying to process so many events that it's becoming overwhelmed.

For example, you're publishing 277.56 Million events compared to 1.41 million subscriptions. 

Can you please check several assessment deliveries that are not being proctored and see if events are enabled?  And can you also please tell us where you're specifying latest? Which API and/or property?

Thanks,
Rich

Hi Hugo,

We looked into the link you sent, specifically, and this may be expected behavior, and possibly for the reason I described. Each connection will timeout after 25 seconds without activity. This is by design and is a bit like hanging up the phone when there's no one there. So this may not be a timeout in the way most people think, where a connection is being denied. Instead, it may just be closing an unused connection, which you will see throughout the use of Events--correct behavior, by design.

We saw a subscription and no publishes. Is there supposed to be an active proctoring session going on now? 

My prior stats were for access_logging. For access_control, we see 151.26 million subscriptions but only 0.19 million publishes. 800x subscribe to publish seems disproportionately high. 

It might be a good idea to setup a call that one of our engineers can join. Can you see if it's possible to get some of your lead developers, that might have visibility on this code, to join a call between 5 and 7pm some time next week? That's a rough window that aligns time zones, and we can get more specific if you want to suggest a few possible meeting times.

Thanks,
Rich

Hi Rich, 

 Thanks for the reply. 

 About the `latest`, we're using https://events.learnosity.com/?v2019.3.LTS, but I saw that eventbus being called with `latest` in chrome requests, no matter what version we use. So that was my first assumption: "could the divergent version be a problem?" 

 I got confused with the numbers. Did you mean we have more publishes than subscriptions? I think that's expected. 

 The incidence of access to "live progress" is much lower than that of attempted submissions.

When we first built live progress, we were under assumption that events published would be replayed when proctor reached the live progress page and we compute status to show based off past and current events. 

 In my tests, even having a publisher, events continued to return timeout, as if the two sides did not communicate.

Two HAR attached - student and teacher. 

 What email can I invite you? Is monday 5 p.m. NY time good for you?

Hugo,

Latest
We'll raise a ticket about not pinning to a specific version, but latest is the most recent sprint, not assumed to be unstable. IOW, we recommend you pin to an LTS so you don't automatically inherit new features without QA or deployment, but it's not the version that is causing the timeouts.

Timeout
The timeout behavior you're describing is expected, and by design. Every connection will timeout after 25 seconds without activity. The analogy I think I used was hanging up the phone after 25 seconds when no one is on the other line.

Publish vs Subscribe
200x to 800x difference in subscribe <--> publish is not normal, and we think this is why:
  The incidence of access to "live progress" is much lower than that of attempted submissions. When we first built live progress, we were under assumption that events published would be replayed when proctor reached the live progress page and we compute status to show based off past and current events.
  
That is not the case. Live Progress is only for use with live sessions. It cannot be used for historical sessions in any way. Nothing is replayed. Enabling the Events API for any session that is not part of a live session using the Live Activity Status by User report, is adding to the event bus unnecessarily.  Here are the docs, if that helps, with a relevant excerpt:

https://reference.learnosity.com/reports-api/reporttypes#liveActivityStatusByUser
  Note This report is primarily for monitoring student progress during proctored assessments. It is updated based on live interactions of students with their assessments in real time. It should not be used to display, analyze, or control historical sessions. Unless a student is interacting live with their assessment, this report will show that user as inactive and control events for their assessment will be ignored.
  
Please try to make it a priority to look into this setup to make sure you're only enabling events when a proctor launches the Live Activity Status by User report or when a student joins. In any other init, including all non-proctored initial, and all resume, review, etc. inits, the Events API should not be used.

Call with Engineering Team
Monday at 5pm will work for me, but I need to confirm availability with the engineering team. The earliest I will be able to do that is Sunday evening. If the Schoology devs that work on the regular and proctored assessments are available at that time, we can tentatively schedule the call, and then we can reschedule on Monday if that doesn't work.

How does that sound?
Rich

Latest

Actually we're using pinned v2019.3.LTS version for the events API. 

 Publish vs Subscribe/Timeout

I think it would be better to discuss this on a call, anyway, if possible. So we can guarantee that the team understands all the peculiarities of changes in the current implementation. 

 Call with Engineering Team

Okay, I'll leave it as "tentative" then. What email can I invite you to?

Hi Hugo,

Because I'm not sure who will be joining, and will know Sunday if the call needs to be changed, I'll send you an invite and then adjust it as needed. 

We just need to be sure we all know today that Monday at 5 is pencilled in and, if we reschedule, we'll wait to hear a confirmation from you that you can attend the preferred time or an alternate time.

I'll send the TBC invite now, and you can add anyone you like.

Thanks,
Rich

Hi Rich, 

 Perfect. I'll let the team know.

Is there any way to reset the tracking on your side for our dev keys while we explore solutions? 

 Thanks!

Hi Hugo,

I'm not sure what that means. What do you mean by reset the tracking?

Rich

Hi Rich, 

 I'm talking about this because of the current behavior. Not even with active subscribers and publishes we can see the "live progress". I attached a video to exemplify the current scenario.

Is there any way to minimize the current impact of the high amount of current publishes? Something that can be reset, perhaps? Just guessing. 

 Thanks!

Hi Hugo,

No, there's no "tracking" or "quota" or similar that is reset. If something is wrong with the use of the report, we can look at that. The overarching issue is just one of volume being sent by your assessments.

All you need to do to stop the unrelated traffic is use the Events API only when starting/joining a Live Activity Status by User report. Don't add events:true for any other assessment, and don't init the Events API directly.

Can we have access to both pages you showed in your video? The first post in this ticket provides info for accessing the proctor, but not adding a live student assessment to that session.

Rich

Hi Rich, 

 Got it, I'll check it. Thank you. 

 I'm sorry, I forgot the student credentials:

User - s100@atal.test

Password - password

Same assessment url: https://app.schoology.com/course/975623930/assessments/975624346 

 Thanks!

Hi Hugo, 

We discussed this during our call and a few things are being considered to reduct he traffic in the Schoology events bus. As there's no other resolution, I think we should close this ticket related to timeouts. Do you agree?

Thanks,
Rich

Hi Rich, 

 Sorry for the lack of communication. I was just waiting for the fix to be released to inform you and close it.

As the event changes will be in today's release, we can close this ticket. :) 

 Thanks,

Hugo.

Hi Rahul,

You can use a feature called lazyload to make long assessments appear to the student faster, in batches.

This improves performance by allowing the student to start the assessment while the other Items are being loaded in the background.

You can use LazyLoad by setting the option to true in your initialization request.

Please have a look through these resources: 
Using Lazy Rendering for Your Assessments

https://reference.learnosity.com/items-api/initialization#config_configuration
lazyload
Type: boolean
Enables lazy loading of items from the Item Bank to improve loading time during API initialization.
Default: false

Here are some lazyload events to use:
https://reference.learnosity.com/items-api/events#assessmentEvents.items.lazyload.batch

I hope this helps.

Hi,  

 We do not want to load all the questions but want to load some questions on demand basis. Like if there are 100 questions and we want to load first 3 questions only. And if user navigate further then only load next question data only. Is there a way to do that? Lazy loading does not seems to be ideal way for our case as anyways it is going to load all the 100 questions which we do not want here. Please let us know if it is possible.

Hi Rahul,

Another option would be to programmatically add items by using the addItems public method. This will allow you to initialize with a few items then add items as the user progresses within this session.

You will just need to come up with the logic on how to know what items will be loaded and when to add them.

Sample script to add items after initialization:
 itemsApp.addItems(
  {
     "items":["item_ref_1", "item_ref_2", "item_ref_3"],
     "removePreviousItems": false
  }
)
 I'd just like to note, we've added a new method for v2020.1.LTS that will be able to tell you if you are on the last item. It returns a boolean value of true/false depending on which item you are currently on.
 itemsApp.getCurrentItem().is_last_item
 I hope this helps.

 I understand that the items won't be duplicated through the program and if the same item exists with the same referenceID; it will just get updated. 

 However, my question revolves around the second aspect of our usage which is if an item in manually created in Learnosity.. we want to detect such items through our program for duplicates as well. I guess the idea here would be set the referenceID correctly. 

 Although, I am confused because through my program and using the LearnositySDK; the way we upload right now is 1). We upload all shared passages 2). We upload all the questions 3). We create a new item and just map the questionID and featureIDs to link passage and question to this item. 

 Is there a similar support in the Learnosity app? I don't see any interface that just lets you create a shared passage or a question and assign referenceIDs to them individually? 

 Could you guys suggest a viable way to possibly detect the manually created items using the SDK? 

 Please let me know! 

 Thanks,

Manish

Hi Manish,

We are looking into this and one of our team will be back with more information.

Kind Regards,
Learnosity Support Team

Hello Manish,

In Author API as in the Author site, questions and features are created from the item_edit view.

If I understand well, you'd like to check if a question or item reference already exists, before creating a new one ?

An easy way of doing so would be using Data API, and sending a request with the given ID to see if it returns something at all.

ie. using the /itembank/items endpoint, you can check if a given item_reference already exists: https://reference.learnosity.com/data-api/endpoints/itembank_endpoints#getItems
Same goes for the /itembank/features endpoint: https://reference.learnosity.com/data-api/endpoints/itembank_endpoints#getFeatures
Or the /itembank/questions endpoint: https://reference.learnosity.com/data-api/endpoints/itembank_endpoints#getQuestions

Would this suit your needs?
Please let me know if I left anything unclear or if you have any further question.


Kind regards,

Angel

Hello Angel, 

 Thanks for sending that. Does our manual content need to be created in a specific way so that it can be searched by the program? One confusion I still have is that when you create an item in the Author site; it allows you to create both passage and the question item but DOES NOT let you assign individual referenceIDs to the passage and the questionID? 

 Another question, when I upload the items through our program I upload the features/passages first with a referenceID (PassageID) and the questions later with referenceID (quesQuestionID). However, when I go in the author site I can only search by the "main" itemID. I can't really search by the "PassageID" or the "quesQuestionID" - meaning I don't see individual passages or questions - I just see the item as whole.  

 How do I know what the is ID of the manually created passages or questions? I understand you can view the referenceID of the main item (but I am puzzled about those individual pieces). 

 I hope I am making sense. If I am misunderstanding something; please correct me. Thank you so much for your help in advance. 

 Manish

Hello Manish,

When using the Author Site, the questions and features are not standalone, meaning they only exist within an item. Hence why when using the Author Site, you won't see the questions and features IDs (reference), and can't assign them yourself; they're created and assigned in the background.

The only way to get these is using Data API. For exemple, you can request questions from the /itembank/questions and filter by the item_reference, to get the questions of this specific item.

When we want to get a question or feature's ID, there can be different ways to do it, depending on the context, and of which API you're working with.


Could you please explain me in further details your context and what you need to achieve? So far I came to the understanding that you're creating content both from the Author Site and from Data API, right?  I'd like to understand how they fit together, and if there's maybe a difference between content created through the author site VS content created through Data API?

Thank you

Kind regards,
Angel

Hi Hannah,

If you're doing this for your stem you can use &#44; instead of the comma, but you should not use that in math expression or they may not be scored correctly (&#44; won't be recognized as a comma by the scoring engine).

To illustrate that point, if you created the following data table:
​

The cell with 7&#44;000 in it would display the way you want it to in the stem: 
​
but if you also used it in the template for the response, you'd get this:
​
So, if you're looking to display text according to your styling conventions in the stem, you can use &#44;​ as a workaround, but you shouldn't use it in expressions that need to be evaluated.

I hope this helps.

Thank you so much!

The solution is quite simple. We change the question validation and simply set the sessions' statuses to "Completed" (even if they already are).

The submissions would be rescored and sent through our kinesis to be processed. It seems it works properly in development (93), but not in staging (485 or 154).

This is an example of a session id:
38a8baef-9db5-5cc0-87b1-8b14513aa876
Initial score was 100, but now it should be 0.

Am I missing anything?

Hey, 

 We're rolling out a rescoring solution and what we've been testing and working fine in dev env, but it doesn't seem to be working in prod env. 

 The solution is quite simple. We change the question validation and simply set the sessions' statuses to "Completed" (even if they already are). 

 The submissions would be rescored and sent through our kinesis to be processed. It seems it works properly in development (93), but not in staging (485 or 154). 

 This is an example of a session id:

38a8baef-9db5-5cc0-87b1-8b14513aa876

Initial score was 100, but now it should be 0. 

 Am I missing anything?

Hi Erik,

The workflow itself sounds good, and there shouldn't be a difference in due to the consumers themselves.

I had a look at that session and it doesn't look like the score changed at all. 

Would you mind sharing the request you're using to make the change?

The only obvious potential pitfall that comes to mind before seeing that is that it looks like that session is stored in your production consumer, so as long as you're using that one you should be able to change the score. If you used your staging consumer, it wouldn't find the session.

-- Horacio

I couldn't find the exact request we sent, does item id help?

6234566d-e880-50a0-b01c-25d13d64a26e

I just tried getting its definition from sessions/templates and the validation was updated. I created similar questions, the session I sent you answered a different one, but I checked it too. 

 Sending user session and question template. 

 Notice in question template that user responded 0, but the validation changed to 2.

Erik, 

Do you mean you change the validation object in the question in the live item bank?

Rich

Hey Rich, 

 Precisely, then I call jobs/sessions/statuses with sessions that has responses to changed question and status "Complete". They are rescored and sent through our kinesis. 

 It's working in an item bank of type "Testing/QA/Staging", but not in one of type "Production". I was thinking it would be due to different caching strategies. 

 By working I mean the score is updated, in prod the score doesn't change.

Hey Horacio and Rich,  

 any updates here?

Hi Erik,

Sorry about the delay here, we were trying to understand what could be going on.

To give you some context, we don't have a mechanism to update the scores from changes in the item bank, so if you changed for example the correct response or the score in the question's validation object, we would be blind to that when we rescore the session and the scoring engine would rescore against what was captured not what is current in the item bank.

Normally, the way to change the score would be to manually set it rather than to have us rescore the session.

In practice that would translate to using this endpoint to tell us "make that score 4".

It may be possible to set up a more complex custom flow to have us score the question by piecing together a few different things first and then manually making a request against the scoring engine and manually updating the score (though that's off the top of my head and untested, there may be pitfalls there to consider).

Having said that, changing the status and sending the session back to our scoring engine should never be influenced by the content in the item bank, but what was captured and recorded when the session was taken.

In other words, if you had: 
  set the correct response of a multiple choice question to be A   taken and submit the assessment  changed the correct response to be B  rescored the session by changing the status  
That session would be rescored against "correct answer: A" because that's what we captured when the assessment was taken.

Is what what your flow currently looks like? If so it shouldn't be returning scores against your new question definition for existing session, only for sessions going forward.

-- Horacio

Hey Horacio, 

 Thanks for the reply. 

 Manually scoring was the initial plan and while we had this discussion I reimplemented it. What was odd to me, though, is that it was working fine in our dev item bank. That's why we moved away from manual scoring until we noticed it wasn't working on prod bank. 

 If I change the validation in the item bank and push a status update with "Completed" it rescores against new validation.

Hi Erik,

You're using v2019.3.LTS in with your dev consumer right? 

I ask because I'm trying to reproduce the successful rescore from item bank data, because if that is happening right now and it is default behavior it may actually be an unintentional breaking change.

Would you mind sharing the portion of the code you're using for that rescore if possible? I'd like to make sure we're not missing anything.

Thank you very much,
-- Horacio
Yep, but we're using that version in both envs, actually.

We weren't performing rescoring, per se, the path we're trying to use is. 

 We hit itembank/questions with an updated definition.

We hit jobs/sessions/statuses with session we want to have rescored and status "Completed". 

 On Learnosity side (in dev env), reprocess session calculating score based on definition we updated, then sends through kinesis for us to save the new score. 

 Both endpoints in both envs are 2019.3.LTS

Hi Erik,

At the pace we move it sometimes happens that the Engineering or Product teams manage to squeeze in a change when there's unexpected room in a sprint, and something changes before Support knows about it. But, to the best of our knowledge, the workflow you're describing does not work.

As far as we're aware, it's not possible to rescore a session by updating the item bank and then submitting the session again. We just tested this and we think we've confirmed our understanding.

This is a critical workflow to prevent unexpected, and ongoing, rescoring every time an author makes a change. For example, customers must be able to check on the status of any in-progress session, so a session is sent through the scoring queue with every save. If a student is working through a resumable session--perhaps saving and returning to it over hours, or even days--it's entirely possible that an author could be editing the item bank during that period. If rescoring was based on live item bank content, item scores could change during a session based not only on intentional updates, but even author error.

Score overrides are accomplished using the Update Response Scores endpoint--not only for adding grades for manually scored question types, but for overriding auto-scored grades in cases of authoring errors and similar situations. 

If you need to calculate a score, you can use the Data API Scoring endpoint. This is not typically in cases where corrections to questions are made because you run into the problem where the student answered A based on the question provided, but might have answered B if the question had been worded differently. However, it can come in handy when a question was worded correctly, and only the answer provided was incorrect. In that case, when only the validation object changes, human intervention/judgment about how the question was answered likely isn't needed, and the response can be scored against the newly edited validation object.

Sorry this ended up on the long side, but I wanted to make sure the workflow, and historical reasons for its design, were clear.  It may be that your testing results seemed to correct content based on item bank changes, but did so for different reasons. It's even possible that Support isn't aware of a change that engineering may have snuck past.

Can you please carefully verify the results you saw in your dev environment. There's no functional distinction in our ecosystem between an environment marked as Tested/QA/Staging and one marked as Production, so we're not sure what would differ that would cause different results.

Thanks,
Rich

Hey Rich. 

 Closing this as we discussed in meeting.

Rich Shupe​ - Actually, in the meeting, didn't we agree to follow up on this with Erik? Specifically, we want to get the request and response for his (we think, mistaken) approach to rescoring that sets session status to 'Completed' instead of using the Update Response Scores endpoint. We'll either uncover unexpected behavior on our end, or (re-)educate him on scoring and Question capture behavior.

Chris Perdue​ I think we came to an implied agreement that it wouldn't work and should let them come back to us if needed. We don't want to shine a light on the testing methodology, but do want to help if they have any additional needs.

Hi Michael,

I just sent the below to Ben Loft:

  Hi Ben, thanks for those details. I can see the cause now.  
  The race condition is happening because of a loading optimization in our APIs. It looks like something in your code is making a local reference to window.LearnosityReports immediately once reports-au.learnosity.com finishes loading. Then your init call happens against this local reference instead of the global window.LearnosityReports object.  
  To fix the issue, can you try changing your code to call the global window.LearnosityReports.init() instead of using your local var?  
  For the detail on why this causes the problem:   reports-au.learnosity.com is a very lightweight script that declares window.LearnosityReports as a shell object which knows how to cache any calls you make to init(). Then it starts loading the full LearnosityReports code asynchronously. This way, the Learnosity script tag loads fast and doesn't block any other scripts/UI inits in your app.  Once the full LearnosityReports code is loaded, it reassigns the value of window.LearnosityReports to be the proper app and then processes any cached init() calls.  When you create your own local reference to window.LearnosityReports, it's pointing at the shell object. So when you call init(), that call goes in the cache list. But by that time, the full app may have already loaded and processed the (empty) cache list, swapped itself into the window.LearnosityReports global, and thereafter it never checks for cached calls again.   
  Please let me know if that solves your issue -- I'll also update the ZD ticket now with a copy of this email.

The limit of 100 should not apply to Pearson Lightbook; they should be grandfathered under the old limits of up to 1000. Full details here: https://learnosity.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DEV/pages/557331/Reports+API

Their choice to use a new consumer each year means their 2020 consumer was created with the new limits of 100. As per that article ^^, you can revert them to the grandfathered limits by simply deleting the Reports API limit CSOs from their 2020 consumer.

Hi - I'm wondering if there is any way to tag metadata at the question level, rather than the item level. We often build multi-part items that need distinct data tags at the question level.

Many thanks,
Travis

Hi - I'm wondering if there is any way to tag metadata at the question level, rather than the item level. We often build multi-part items that need distinct data tags at the question level. 

 Many thanks,

Travis

Hi Travis,

It depends on the metadata. Learnosity tags are stored at the item or activity levels, it's not possible to attach them to a question.

That means that any of our reports, adaptive logic, or endpoints that use tags will only look for them in items or activities.

Having said that, it is possible to add metadata of other types to the question level. It's actually even possible to add UI fields for it in the question editor (more on that here).

If you'd like to add it programmatically and are embedding Author API (which I believe you are, but I may be wrong), you can use this public method as well: https://reference.learnosity.com/author-api/methods#setWidget

If you have any questions, please let me know. I'm happy to expand on anything.

Kind regards,
-- Horacio

Thanks for the quick response, Horacio. So, are you suggesting something like the attached image where we add a field to the question level?  

 Can you give me an example of this being done previously?

Hi Travis,

Yes, almost exactly that, only it would be a little below where it is in your image:
​​

There's a Custom Metadata section that appears when that extra metadata is added to hold the new fields.

My image comes from an internal Learnosity item bank and that metadata was probably used for some kind of testing (in this case they all look like already existing fields, so some of our engineers may have been testing potential clashes in the question's definition).

-- Horacio

This is in the Curriculum Associates - Authoring [20] item bank.

Hi Mutya, 

 As you can imagine this is a pretty critical issue where we have accidentally reverted up to around 1000 items. We'd really appreciate any insights you can provide at this time. Our editorial team is waiting on additional edits that are required for these items until we learn more about any possible fixes/solutions you may have to help. This content is critical for our back to school release, so any hold up is concerning for our editors.  

 I appreciate your attention to this issue. 

 Thanks,

Lauren

Hi Lauren,

I'm afraid we don't have a way of rolling back customer content changes. If you use item pools, however, you can pull the data from the item pool and restore the live bank that way.

We have some form of catastrophic (rather than on-demand) data recovery options--for example for loss of an entire item bank--but these are at the AWS level, and are significant in time, effort, and likely expense. It's not something we can do immediately, and it still has to be approved.

Sorry we don't have a better answer,
Rich
Thanks for the info Rich. We will explore more manual solutions on our end.
Sure, Lauren, thanks.

This is a follow-up to your previous request #12569 "Resuming data api queries".

Hi. This doesn't do exactly what we need. For example, if I recursively request a total of 60 records on the questions endpoint, on the first request I will get 50 along with a next record. On the subsequent request I will pass that value and get 10 records, but no next property will be available in the meta object for that response. When I attempt to execute a later request based on the last "next" property I received I will get those same 10 records again, plus any new records. Can you confirm if this is a bug or expected behavior?

Thanks,

Scott

This is a follow-up to your previous request #12569 "Resuming data api queries". 

 Hi. This doesn't do exactly what we need. For example, if I recursively request a total of 60 records on the questions endpoint, on the first request I will get 50 along with a next record. On the subsequent request I will pass that value and get 10 records, but no next property will be available in the meta object for that response. When I attempt to execute a later request based on the last "next" property I received I will get those same 10 records again, plus any new records. Can you confirm if this is a bug or expected behavior? 

 Thanks, 

 Scott

Hello Scott,

That's the expected behavior, there's no next token at the last return because we don't expect clients to pick up where they left off when it comes to content (the way they might with sessions they may need to download to update student's scores, for example).

I don't believe we have an out of the box way of identifying the next set of questions other than perhaps checking the dt_created of the questions you receive if you use the last pagination next token against the timestamp returned on the last set of questions (if you expect them to have been created after your last get).

Would you mind sharing your use case for saving all the questions locally? I'd like to share it internally if possible in case it's something we should consider as a potential future change.

Thank you,
-- Horacio

We are pulling records from sessions and lining that up with tags, activities and questions so we can perform analysis over that data. We would like to pull information incrementally over the itembank endpoints tags, activities and questions.  For activities we can sort by last updated and then filter based on a maxTime parameter. Not sure how this could be possible with questions though. 

 -Scott

I meant *minTime* parameter 

 -Scott

Hi Scott,

I ran some tests and mintime is working with the itembank/questions endpoint, so right now a request like this one would get you the questions created today since 12:00:00 GMT:
 {
        "mintime":"2020-05-05 12:00:00"
}
 
Having said that, that's not documented and I'd like to confirm that the lack of documentation is an oversight and that this is something that you can rely on and that we are going to support.

I'll confirm as soon as I hear back from the Data API team.

-- Horacio

Jordan Hume​ -- Are we happy to support mintime and maxtime in the itembank/questions endpoint?

They seem to work and they're not documented. I acknowledged the option since he was already trying to use it, but I'd prefer to tell him "don't do that or things may break" if necessary.
Thank you. That would be appreciated

Hi Scott,

I got confirmation that the lack of documentation is an oversight and we include mintime in our tests.

It should be safe for you to use it in your requests and I'll open an internal ticket so our documentation team adds it to our reference site.

Kind regards,
-- Horacio
Excellent. Thank you.

Hello!

We currently implemented some "simple features" in Schoology assessments and it's performing really well.
We have a copy feature in assessments that duplicates the questions with an additional prefix of "COPY -".

It turns out that when we try to duplicate a question that has a "simple feature" in the "stimulus", such as video or audio, the text "Unknown Feature type" is displayed instead of loading the component in the copy.
I believe there is an association of the question with the simple feature, since an id is generated.

Is there any way to duplicate this content, based on the id?

Thanks,
Hugo Blanco.

Hello! 

 We currently implemented some "simple features" in Schoology assessments and it's performing really well.

We have a copy feature in assessments that duplicates the questions with an additional prefix of "COPY -". 

 It turns out that when we try to duplicate a question that has a "simple feature" in the "stimulus", such as video or audio, the text "Unknown Feature type" is displayed instead of loading the component in the copy.

I believe there is an association of the question with the simple feature, since an id is generated. 

 Is there any way to duplicate this content, based on the id? 

 Thanks,

Hugo Blanco.

Hi Hugo,

The ID is used to tie to a feature called "Action Builder" that allows you to automate certain actions (for example, "when audio player '123' is done playing, enable the multiple choice question '456'").

You should be able to edit the ID (or reuse one used in the original question) without getting an error. 

There is a data-type="audioplayer"value that, if edited or removed, would result in an error like the one from your screenshot.

I'd ask to see an item so I can tell you more, but I think that error actually shows that the simple feature wasn't recognized so it couldn't be added, so there likely wouldn't be anything there.

Is there any way you'd be able to log the request right before you send it to the API to see what the simple feature tag looks like in the request?

Thank you,
-- Horacio

Hi Horacio, 

 Now that you said it, I actually found this property missing from the copy. I think that this correction will have to be done on our side. 

 So wouldn't it be a problem to reuse the same simple feature in a copy? 

 Thanks,

Hugo Blanco.

Hi Hugo,

The simple feature's ID won't be tied to the question so it should load.   A potential problem I see is if you wanted to have both questions in a single item, in which case Action Builder may have trouble targeting the right one if you want to add any kind of automation. 

You could run into a similar problem if both questions are in the same activity and you have any kind of custom code on the page to automatically play the audio or respond to the audio being played, since that would need to use the ID to find the audio player.

It would probably be better if you gave it a different random UUID when you create it if you think anything like that could potentially happen, but the question itself should load fine even if the ID is the same. 

That ID is meant to be a unique identifier within the current context, but the simple feature is not stored individually in our databases the way questions that are part of an item are (or items that are part of an activity), it's just stored as component of the question the same way the stimulus, or the correct response are.

I hope that helps,
-- Horacio

Hi Horacio, 

 Got it. It makes sense.

I don't think this behavior could cause us any trouble in the short term. So we're good to keep as is. :) 

 It helped a lot. Thank you! 

 Hugo Blanco.

subject: Moving from Test account to Production Account

comments.body:
Hi We have been using the test account for quite some time, and now we want to iteratively move to the Production environment. I'd like to know the procedures to migrate the data and the procedure to integrate the new prod environment.

Also can I use test account and prod account simultaneously?

Hi We have been using the test account for quite some time, and now we want to iteratively move to the Production environment. I'd like to know the procedures to migrate the data and the procedure to integrate the new prod environment. 

 Also can I use test account and prod account simultaneously?

Hi Udit,

We are looking into this and one of our team will be back with more information.

Kind Regards,
Learnosity Support Team

Hi Udit,

Can you clarify what kind of data you are hoping to migrate?

I have outlined the steps below to migrate Itembank data. If you are happy with these steps, I can provision your new Production consumer.
Once this has been provisioned, you will get a new consumer key and secret to start using in your Production environment. You can keep using your testing consumer for development and testing purposes. 


 Copying Data from one Itembank to another To get started, you want to initialize a Data API instance both for the source item bank (using the consumer credentials for the item bank you'll be copying the content from) and destination item bank (using the credentials for the item bank you'll be copying to). For each Learnosity data type (questions, items, activities, etc.), you'll then want to use a get endpoint for the source bank and a set endpoint for the destination bank.
Note: The order of these operations can be important. For example, because items contain questions and/or features, those questions/features must exist prior to creating the items. Similarly, items must be created before activities can contain them.
1. Migrate tags. While tags can be created on the fly in some cases, it's probably clearest to pre-create them as the first step in your migration, make sure all tag types and tag names exist before saving all items or activities.
a. getTags
b. setTags

Note: We do not have an endpoint for creating Tag Hierarchies so this needs to be done manually via our Author Site. See here for more information about creating hierarchies, and the Tag Hierarchy Manager role.
2. Migrate questions and features. You can do this using a list of question or feature references (appropriate for each endpoint), if you have them. Alternately, you can pass item references to each endpoint and get back the questions or features (again, depending on which endpoint you're using) associated with that item.
a. getQuestions
b. setQuestions
c. getFeatures
d. setFeatures

3. Migrate items and activities. Remember to create any required questions and features before items, and items before activities. You may also choose to further limit items and/or activities using the status values: ["published", "unpublished", "archived"]. For example, you may want to only copy published content, or perhaps exclude all archived content.
a. getItems (use include object to include dynamic data)
b. setItems
c. getActivities
d. setActivities

A few additional points:
Assets referenced by questions/items/features (such as images, audio, and video files, for example) will not be copied with the JSON you are migrating. If desired, you can use this uploadAssets endpoint to bulk upload assets. Absolute references to assets will still work across organizations.
We recommend copying data in batches of 50 and repeating the process until complete. See your SDK of choice for more info, using requestRecursive() or the next token, as specified in the SDK.

Let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks,
Conor

Hi Conor, it looks good. We'd like to have a new Production Consumer. 

 Also, can we have another Test Account?

Hi Udit,

  it looks good. We'd like to have a new Production Consumer.
  No problem, I'll look into getting this set up.

  Also, can we have another Test Account?
  Can you please explain why you would need another testing consumer?
Consumers are used to segregate the storage of student responses and sessions. Normally, we provision clients with one consumer for testing purposes and one for production. Additional consumers may come at a cost, and a member of our customer success team would need to speak with someone from Cuemath before proceeding with a third consumer.

Thanks,
Conor

Hi Rich Shupe​ 
Did you need to check something here before we provision the new consumer?

They only have one consumer at the minute, used for development. They are looking for one for Production.

They also mentioned wanting a third consumer, but didn't respond when I questioned why.

Reassigning this to you so you see it
No, I just wanted to know about the third consumer, and your response was perfect.

subject: New question type: "Set commas correctly in a sentence"

comments.body:
Dear Learnosity-Team,

I have request for a new question type, where the correct placement of a comma in a sentence can be practiced. In the current pool of question types, I hardly can do it, isn't it? Most likely with "Fill in the blanks". However, I would have to add a blank after each word in the sentence and also an empty blank must be counted as correct, if no comma is necessary. 
So, I would suggest a completely new question type, which works like this: A sentence is given, where perhaps some commas are missing. There should be the possibility to drag the commas in between each word of the sentence. Also an empty blank should be validated as correct, if no comma is necessary there.

Such a question type is highly required by our customers ((German) language teachers) and we would love to provide them this question type.

I am looking forward to hear from you.

Thank you and best regards,
Stephan

There should be the possibility to drag the commas in between each word of the sentence. Also an empty blank should be validated as correct, if no comma is necessary there.

I'll let you know if I have any questions.

Original ticket raised by Stephan Gleich at NE Nationalencyklopedin

Issue
New Question Type - Placement of Punctuation

Priority context
Medium

Client Context
NE Nationalencyklopedin

Detailed Feature Description
As a client, I want a question type which easily validates the placement of punctuation in a sentence, because it is highly required by some of our customers German language teachers.
I would suggest a completely new question type, which works like this: A sentence is given, where perhaps some commas are missing. There should be the possibility to drag the commas in between each word of the sentence. Also an empty blank should be validated as correct, if no comma is necessary there.

It is currently possible to create something similar with "Fill in the blanks". However, this would require a blank space after each word in the sentence.

Hi Stephan,

The PO and dev team have reviewed your Feature Request for a new question type for the placement of punctuation in a sentence.
Unfortunately, they have decided not to add it to the near term roadmap, although will consider it again in the future.

As you suggested below, you could achieve something similar using 'fill in the blanks'.
Alternatively, you could use the Drawing Question Type (but this has the drawback of not being auto-scorable).

I will close this ticket now. If you have any questions, feel free to reopen it.

Thanks,
Conor

Hi Conor,

thank you very much for letting me know.

It's a pity that my idea is not considered for the near time roadmap. But I am happy that they will have it in mind for the future. 

 Thanks also for suggesting me an alternative. I will test, whether it works with the drawing question type "Highlight image". 

 Best regards,

Stephan

Hi Stephan,

Image Highlight and Drawing are two different question types. So you could investigate both and see if any of them work for you :)

I'll close this ticket now. If you have any questions, feel free to reopen it, or to open a new ticket.

Thanks,
Conor

Can you confirm that your drag and drop activities are WCAG / ADA compliant?  I believe they are, but wanted to confirm before I responded to a customer who had a question about it.

Hi Derek,

The drag and drop question types are accessible (keyboard navigable, screenreader-friendly, etc), if you have a specific WCAG standard that you're testing against I can find out if there are any known issues. 

I believe we are guided by WCAG 2.1 AA whenever possible (the exceptions are typically question types like drawing which is not easy to make compatible with screen readers for example, and some older graphing question types that are getting an accessibility upgrade right now).

By the way, in case it could be useful to you, 2e are currently awaiting the results of an external accessibility audit which will allow us to publish a VPAT with more details on our compliance, there will be a general announcement once it's ready but it should be relatively soon (at that latest with our next LTS release, but likely earlier than that).

Kind regards,
-- Horacio

Thanks for the confirmation, Horatio. That’s what I needed. 

 Hope you’re well.

You're very welcome. 

And thank you, same to you.

subject: Difference Between Item Type and Interaction Type

comments.body: I'm a Tech Coach at Otus, currently working with our dev team on updating our integration with Learnosity (as well as the Navigate item bank). I'm looking for resources that detail the differences between "Item Type" and "Interaction Type," but so far have been unsuccessful. Could you please point me in the right direction, and/or let me know if this question is best answered by Navigate? Thank you in advance!

I'm a Tech Coach at Otus, currently working with our dev team on updating our integration with Learnosity (as well as the Navigate item bank). I'm looking for resources that detail the differences between "Item Type" and "Interaction Type," but so far have been unsuccessful. Could you please point me in the right direction, and/or let me know if this question is best answered by Navigate? Thank you in advance!

Hi Matt,

Learnosity doesn't have a concept of an Item Type or an Interaction Type so I had a quick look at the Navigate item bank and it looks like they're setting each as tags. 

That means that they would be the best people to contact to explain that, since we don't really have any insight on their tags and what they signify.

I hope that helps,
-- Horacio

Hello Horacio, 

 Thank you - I appreciate the response! At least I know what path to follow. 

 Have a good day,

Matt 

 Matt Frank

Technology Coach

773-789-5444 x143
Thank you, you too!

subject: User receives 500 internal server error when uploading pictures to items

comments.body: mmalloy@cusd201.org receives a 500 internal server error when uploading images to any items. She generated an HAR file for us.
mmalloy@cusd201.org receives a 500 internal server error when uploading images to any items. She generated an HAR file for us.

Hi Phil,

Thank you for the HAR file I'll have a look at it and get back to you with what I find.

Kind regards,
-- Horacio
ICAP error, there's some content filtering going on...

Hi Phil, 

This is the error recorded on the network call throwing the 500:
 <!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=http://97.64.60.4/ibreports/ibp/bp.html?bu=https://authorapi.learnosity.com/v2019.3.LTS/assets/uploadform&bc=The%20requested%20URL%20could%20not%20be%20retrieved.&ip=65.60.144.49&er=ERR_ICAP_FAILURE"/>
</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>
 The ERR_ICAP_FAILURE refers to this network protocol: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Content_Adaptation_Protocol

ICAP is used by caching proxies and is often used for content filtering (think: blocking Netflix at an office or Instagram at a school).

I ran a quick search on the IP address reported in this part of the error:
  http://97.64.60.4/ibreports/ibp/bp.html
 and I got this back:
 Source: whois.arin.net
IP Address: 97.64.60.4
Name: IBOSS-8
Handle: NET-97-64-48-0-1
Registration Date: 5/18/17
Range: 97.64.48.0-97.64.63.255
Org: iboss,inc
Org Handle: IBOSS-8
Address: 101 Federal St
City: Boston
State/Province: MA
Postal Code: 02110
Country: United States
 So it looks like the IP address is in use by this company: https://www.iboss.com/

It looks like what's happening to this user is that they're using a network that is using iBoss to block domains that haven't been whitelisted, or that doesn't have their caching policy properly set up (this is a complete guess but I suspect the "upload" in the URL may be clashing with some security policy that has been put into the place).

Either way, it doesn't look like something you'll be able to fix on your end.

If this is the same user you mentioned in an earlier ticket, I think you (or Monica) had mentioned that she was working from home, so a VPN could be what's redirecting the request to iBoss.

I hope that helps shed some light on the issue, especially considering that if it is the same user I know you've been dealing with this for a weeks now without being able to reproduce (which I know very well can be a challenge).

Kind regards,
-- Horacio
Thank you! I relayed the information to our user so that hopefully her IT department can help.

subject: Editing tools in responses for MC, Cloze with text, etc.

comments.body: I need the ability to apply styles (ital, super- and  subscript, bold, etc.) to responses in many of the question formats. It is available for sort lists and other questions types.
I need the ability to apply styles (ital, super- and  subscript, bold, etc.) to responses in many of the question formats. It is available for sort lists and other questions types.

Hi Kerriebeth,

Most questions types (including Sort list) do support rich text formatting. The options will simply appear over the field you're editing when you click on it like this:
​​

There are some extra buttons in the bar that are more Learnosity-specific, you can see an overview of what those do here, but the formatting ones are the standard ones you'll find in most texted editors (B, I, size, bulleted and numbered lists, etc). Sub and superscripts can be found under the "Styles" dropdown menu.

If the question doesn't automatically present that menu, it doesn't support rich text formatting. The only ones that I know off the top of my head that do not support it are the ones that use dropdown menus, for example, "cloze with drop down" (the behavior is not consistent across browser and devices, so the Product team opted to omit those to provide a predictable experience until there is a standard).

I hope that helps,
-- Horacio

Hi, Horacio, 

 Thank you for such a quick response! I know that there are other response types that offer the styling (and I've used them), but I need it for the ones I mentioned as well. I'm working on a chemistry book and it's important that I have a variety of question types and that the elements are correctly presented. I need it in Multiple Choice, Cloze with text, and Cloze drop-down. 

 Thanks,

kb

Hi KB,

Multiple Choice has formatting. If you place your cursor in the editable field, you'll see the rich text editor appear. (It will look like the editor visible in the image Horacio posted about Sort List.) Please let us know if you're referring to a specific part of the question where you don't see this editor.

Cloze with Text can format the response as a whole by selecting response box and formatting that. There is currently no ability to format selectively, with multiple formats in a single response box. We will log a feature request for this. The feature request will then be triaged and, if approved, be slotted for a future development sprint. We want to make sure we don't hold you up, however, so we should say that tf approved, this will take some time and is likely not something that will have an immediate affect on questions you're creating for a current text book.

As Horacio said, Cloze with Drop Down uses native drop down menus for optimal display across all drop down devices. Formatting, special characters, and similar are not supported in this question type. There are no plans for this to change. If these features are critical, you'll need to consider an alternate question type from our 50 or so available.

Thanks,
Rich

subject: have a destroy public method for questions id(s) as input parameters which will delete related div from DOM.

comments.body:

P.S. I will create an internal FEAT ticket here as well for destroy() public method with question ref as input parameter.

Raised from https://learnositysupport.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/8824

P.S. I will create an internal FEAT ticket here as well for destroy() public method with question ref as input parameter.


  Kind Regards,

Dmitry Kochnev

*Case*:
Knewton uses Desmos custom questions to render them on their pages.

Knewton calls Questions API three times (each init call with single question inside). 
Should call one init with three questions inside.

Knewton can not call one init with 3 questions as:
Each presentation of a Learnosity component (or example answer) is its own QuestionsApp.init() instance to squeeze the Learnosity API into the React architecture and our SPA. We could re-architect to have only one Questions instance and use append to add subsequent widgets, but we would also require a remove function, as well. Our architecture defines each presentation of a Learnosity question to be a single component that may load and unload from the page independently from the rest. I'm afraid an append / reset flow doesn't fit that model.


*Temp solution*:
As Questions API were overhauled long time ago to use React as well, my colleagues told me that you can just delete the main question div from DOM and it will trigger internal react cleaning from Questions API. For example, if you have in your HTML initially this span
  <span class="learnosity-response question-demo1-c5d21a93-01d2-43b1-866f-5c060764e86a"></span>
 and once Questions API is rendered and it is replaced by:
 <div id="demo1-c5d21a93-01d2-43b1-866f-5c060764e86a" class="lrn lrn_widget lrn_qr lrn_clearfix lrn_mcq   ">
...
</div>
 
If you delete manually this DIV (by id) from DOM, Questions API react will clean up everything for you.


*feature*:
have a destroy public method for questions id(s) as input parameters which will delete related div from DOM.

But, we have a product requirement where we have to show Live responses from a session. To implement that, we would need a remove functionality or a re-append functionality where we can re-render a question with newer responses without re-initializing the questionsApp object.

Thanks for your time.

subject: Link enhancement in essay based question types

comments.body:
Hi there,
One of our standard use cases for Learnosity based content is delivering it through a locked down browser, ensuring that students are not provided any digital/online helping aids. 

One of our customers have found out that entering a full url to a webpage in the rich text editor in the essay based question type automatically enhances the text to a clickable URL. This makes it possible for the student to navigate to the url afterwards and thereby circumventing parts of the lock down security. 

It is of very high importance that we are able to close this security hole and it seems like a troublesome procedure for us to develop some counteraction to this automatic url enhancing in the WYSIWYG. 

How should we avoid this URL enhancement securely?

Best
Mads

This makes it possible for the student to navigate to the url afterwards and thereby circumventing parts of the lock down security.  

 It is of very high importance that we are able to close this security hole and it seems like a troublesome procedure for us to develop some counteraction to this automatic url enhancing in the WYSIWYG.

Learnosity Support Team

Original ticket raised by Mads Stenhøj Andresen at UNIwise

**Affected APIs & Versions**
Question API

**Issue**
When typing a URL address in rich text editor, the URL is automatically converted to hyperlink

**Priority context**
High

**Client Context**
UNIwise is delivering assessments through a locked down browser, ensuring that students are not provided any digital/online helping aids. Students always find a way...

**Steps to Replicate**
Create a question type Essay with Rich Text.
Type www.google.com as answer in the rich text editor. 

**Expected Behaviour**
The URL will be displayed as plain text.

**Actual Behaviour**
The URL is converted to hyperlink, allowing student to access online helping aids.

**Developer Suggestion**

Hi Mads,

We do not have an out-of-the-box way to prevent URL to be automatically converted to hyperlink.
I raised this issue internally with our teams, and I'll let you know when we have updates.

In the meantime, we'd advise your dev team to look into the idea of adding an event listener on the rich text editor, to search and destroy any <a href=""> tags.

Kind regards,
Angel

Hi Angelique, 

 I have been notified, that it has been almost 2 weeks without an update on this subject. Would it be possible to know where you are with the progress on this issue? 

 Kind regards,

Frederik Hansen

Original ticket raised by Mads Stenhøj Andresen at UNIwise

Issue
Rich Text Editor converts URL to Hyperlink

Priority context
Medium

Client Context
UNIwise

Detailed Feature Description
As a < type of user >, I want < some goal > so that < some reason >.
As a Author, I want to prevent URL to be automatically converted to Hyperlink, so that students cannot leave the assessment and access internet (assessment being delivered in a locked down browser)

NB: Duplicate of LRN-25808, as this was originally raised as a bug but turned out to be a FEAT request.

Hi Angel,

Thanks for your CSS hack; that seems like a quick and effortless way to avoid the links being used. We tried to do the clean up before each save, but it does not seem reliable to remove it in the DOM alone, as the rich text editor does not detect it as a change and thus it is only saved, if you write more afterwards. 

 Furthermore it could be a case that a student actually wanted to write a domain like text; ie. referencing that it could be found in some website and thus it is a little obfuscating that we now removes the link. 

 As I can tell from the html your are using WYSIhtml below for the text area. It looks like it is a simple config option in the init of the editor to disable/enable autolink. Wouldn't you consider providing this option in the learnosity initialisation and then pass it on to WYSIhtml? 

https://github.com/Voog/wysihtml/wiki/Configuration#autolink 

 Best

Mads

Hi Joe,

Custom buttons can be added to any region and used to call customized functionality. The following options are available:

  name - The button name determines the event that is triggered upon clicking.  label - A label bundle reference. If not a default one, it should be specified manually in the label bundle configuration.  icon_class - The CSS class applied to the button, intended to determine the icon used.  
You can customize this button by setting the class yourself.
